cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, as it deals with the task of image captioning that combines both fields. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for generating captions suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the investigation of the influence of model width and depth suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
